            <scopecontent id="aspace_373622a1b2cafff6b03b41db526e3dd2">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Early correspondence (before 1911) relates chiefly to Michigan real estate and includes letters sent to landowners, often in Eastern states, making offers on their holdings in Michigan. Correspondence from the 1900s and 1910s includes documentation of the Judsons' involvement in mining ventures. Much of the later correspondence relates to Nathan Judson's business and personal relationships with his three nephews: Wilber, Lowell, and Paul Judson.</p>
            </scopecontent>
